George Rose (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Rose_(actor) 0 George Walter Rose (19 February 1920 – 5 May 1988) was an English actor and singer in theatre and film. Born in Bicester, Oxfordshire the son of a butcher, Rose studied at the Central School of Speech and Drama. After graduation, he was briefly a farmer and secretary. After wartime service and studies at Oxford, he made his Old Vic stage debut in 1946. George_Walter_Rose ( 19_February_1920 – 5_May_1988 ) was an_English_actor_and_singer in theatre_and_film .
